Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph <uri> {{ predicate }}

URI Predicate Command

Target:
  {{ uri }}

Predicate:
  {{ predicate }}

{% if predicate == "related" %}
Purpose:
  Expand from the current chunk or entity object to nearby objects.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} related [--query <query>] [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--role <any|subject|object|self>] [--evidence [n]] [--json|--jsonl]

Notes:
  - Chunk targets return nearby Reading Graph chunks.
  - Entity targets return Knowledge Graph triples involving the entity.
  - `--query` filters and ranks related results with the current FTS index.
  - `--role` only applies to entity targets.
  - Use `wikigraph {{ uri }} evidence --help` when source grounding is the main goal.
{% elif predicate == "evidence" %}
Purpose:
  Trace the current object back to source-backed evidence.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} evidence [--query <query>] [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl]

Notes:
  - Evidence is for grounding, verification, and citation support.
  - `--query` filters and ranks evidence with the current FTS index.
  - Evidence previews include nearby source context by default; use `--context 0` for exact cited ranges.
  - Source and scope URIs are not evidence targets.
{% elif predicate == "pack" %}
Purpose:
  Build bounded Agent-readable context around the current chunk or entity object.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} pack [--budget <chars>] [--json|--jsonl]

Notes:
  - Default budget is 5000 characters.
  - Use this after selecting a useful chunk or entity.
  - Use `evidence` first when verification matters more than context assembly.
{% elif predicate == "create" %}
Purpose:
  Create or replace the archive at this URI.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} create [source] [--input-format <format>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]

Notes:
  - `source` may be EPUB, Markdown, txt, or another supported input.
  - Stdin is supported when `--input-format markdown` or `--input-format txt` is provided.
{% elif predicate == "export" %}
Purpose:
  Export a projection from this archive.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} export --output-format <format> [--output <path>]

Notes:
  - Projections are portable views; they do not replace the `.wikg` archive.
{% elif predicate == "inspect" %}
Purpose:
  Inspect archive readiness before `--query`, retrieval, or starting generated work.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} inspect

Notes:
  - Run this before broad Reading Graph, Reading Summary, or Knowledge Graph work.
{% elif predicate == "add" and target.name == "chapter-collection-scope" %}
Purpose:
  Add a planned chapter to the archive.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} add [--parent <chapter-uri>] [--title <title>] [--after <chapter-uri>] [--before <chapter-uri>] [--stage planned]
{% elif predicate == "add" and target.name == "job-collection-scope" %}
Purpose:
  Add a local generation job.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} add --input <chapter-uri> --task reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph --accept-cost [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]

Notes:
  - Generation jobs may call an LLM provider and incur cost.
{% elif predicate == "move" %}
Purpose:
  Move this chapter in the chapter tree.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} move [--parent <chapter-uri>] [--after <chapter-uri>] [--before <chapter-uri>]
{% elif predicate == "remove" %}
Purpose:
  Remove this chapter.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} remove [--confirm]
{% elif predicate == "reset" %}
Purpose:
  Delete later-stage artifacts for this chapter.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} reset --to source|reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph [--confirm]
{% elif predicate == "set" %}
Purpose:
  Modify this writable URI target.

{% if target.name == "chapter-tree-object" %}
Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} set --input <tree.json>
{% elif target.name == "chapter-source-object" %}
Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} set [text] [--input <path>] --input-format markdown|txt
{% elif target.name == "chapter-summary-object" %}
Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} set [text] [--input <path>]
{% elif target.name == "chapter-title-object" %}
Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} set <title>
{% elif target.name == "job-target-object" %}
Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} set reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph
{% elif target.name == "local-config-section" %}
Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} set [<json>] [--json <json>|--json-input <json>]
{% else %}
Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} set [options]
{% endif %}
{% elif predicate == "clear" %}
Purpose:
  Clear this writable resource or local config section.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} clear
{% elif predicate == "build" %}
Purpose:
  Build the FTS index for this archive.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} build [--jsonl]
{% elif predicate == "embed" %}
Purpose:
  Store the FTS index inside the archive.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} embed
{% elif predicate == "external" %}
Purpose:
  Keep the FTS index outside the archive as local cache.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} external
{% elif predicate == "clean" %}
Purpose:
  Remove completed local generation jobs.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} clean
{% elif predicate == "watch" %}
Purpose:
  Follow durable local job progress.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} watch [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]
{% elif predicate == "pause" %}
Purpose:
  Pause this local job.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} pause
{% elif predicate == "resume" %}
Purpose:
  Resume this local job.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} resume
{% elif predicate == "cancel" %}
Purpose:
  Cancel this local job.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} cancel
{% elif predicate == "boost" %}
Purpose:
  Move this local job forward in the local job scheduler.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} boost
{% elif predicate == "put" %}
Purpose:
  Set one key in this local config section.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} put <key> <value>
  wikigraph {{ uri }} put <key> --secret
{% elif predicate == "delete" %}
Purpose:
  Delete one key from this local config section.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} delete <key>
{% elif predicate == "test" %}
Purpose:
  Test connectivity for this local config section.

Usage:
  wikigraph {{ uri }} test
{% endif %}

Related help:
  - wikigraph {{ uri }} --help
  - wikigraph help uri
